title.label: Wonderful gameplay but could be amazing

content.label:
I enjoyed the game but with the following tweaks I would be actively recommending it. When playing this game I want:

- to be able to choose my bat for every exercise, not just some. This frustrated me.

- more variety in opponents playing styles. Skill and stamina aren‚Äôt enough, I‚Äôd like to see more variability in offense, defense, spin, etc, so I really have to adapt to new opponents.

- the ability to spend my reputation (or match winnings) on bat upgrades. 

- visuals and stories for my opponents. I like building a narrative in my head when playing.

- a secret bonus level after the world champs. Would add some needed mystique to the game.

- controls that increase my likelihood of hitting the ball when it‚Äôs loving fast. Like other reviews I also felt like the ball passed by when I was certain my finger was in the right place, but I think it‚Äôs because when the ball is going fast you need lots of precision. This is frustrating, not challenging. Instead, if my shot isn‚Äôt quite perfect at high speed I should still be able to hit the ball, but my accuracy or speed of return should suffer.

Give the game these tweaks and you‚Äôll be on to an all-time winner. It‚Äôs so close! Thanks for your good work and attention to detail.
